OL,6,FThe More in Common poll, carried out
OL,7,Fbetween March 8 and 11, also found
OL,8,Fsupport for tougher action against
OL,9,Fthose who promote hate or cause
OL,10,Fsignificant disruption during
OL,11,Fprotests, but did not want to see
OL,12,Fprotests banned altogether.
OL,14,FLuke Tryl, director of More in Common,
OL,15,Fsaid: "These findings should act as a
OL,16,Fwake-up call signalling that the
OL,17,Fpublic is deeply concerned about
OL,18,FIslamist and far-right extremism, and
OL,19,Fthey expect the Government, police and
OL,20,Fothers to take action to tackle
OL,21,Fextremism and those who peddle hate."
